"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0808-1464035-paris-2024-irish-in-action-on-day-14-of-olympic-games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Rhasidat Adelekewill become the first Irish woman to ever compete in an Olympic sprint final on Day 14 of the Paris Games - and the 21-year-old from Tallaght will be targeting a medal at the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 38, \"end\": 43, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9997653217132516, \"rank\": 0.00017673697842784516, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 149, \"end\": 157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tallaght\", \"score\": 0.9999999870738067, \"rank\": 1.2167716023755938e-08, \"text\": \"Tallaght\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tallaght\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tallaght\"}, {\"begin\": 191, \"end\": 206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adeleke secured an automatic place in the 400m final,finishing second in her Wednesday night semi-final with a time of 49.94.\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 334, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her time was the sixth fastest of the eight across the three semi-finals and she will be hoping for a big improvement to be in podium contention.\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland will also be involved in two semi-finals on the track on Friday morning withMark Englishtargeting an 800m final at 10.30am andSarah Lavinin the 100m hurdles shortly after at 11.05am.\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 483, \"end\": 490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999998572263951, \"rank\": 1.4153064064057985e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also on the track will beIreland's women's 4x400m team, who will take part in the second semi-final heat at 9.52am.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The four athletes chosen to compete in the semi-final areSophie Becker,Phil Healy,Kelly McGroryandSharlene Mawdsley.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 856, \"end\": 862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Becker\", \"score\": 0.999851743953284, \"rank\": 0.00012395519742997222, \"text\": \"Becker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Becker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Becker\"}, {\"begin\": 863, \"end\": 873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Healy\", \"score\": 0.9999865515186963, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phil Healy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Healy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Healy\"}, {\"begin\": 874, \"end\": 879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"score\": 0.999999994016207, \"rank\": 5.953743617599835e-09, \"text\": \"Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kate O'Connorwill wrap up a busy day in the Stade de France for Team Ireland when she competes in the closing leg of the women's heptathlon.\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 910, \"end\": 914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9972444570053535, \"rank\": 0.002762706769052032, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 974, \"end\": 986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2945564690770897e-14, \"text\": \"Team Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She will contend the long jump and javelin throw in the morning session before taking part in the 800m in the evening to conclude Day 14.\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland's double-medallistDaniel Wiffenwill compete in his final Olympic event of Paris 2024 when he plunges into the river Seine for the 10km marathon swim.\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1190, \"end\": 1197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999998572263951, \"rank\": 1.4153064064057985e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1272, \"end\": 1282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.769571015821132e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Water quality in the Seine has proved a headache for organisers of these Games, however Thursday's women's event passed without any apparent incident in what would certainly have been a relief for officials.\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999984084, \"rank\": 1.5638792650021151e-12, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When he dives off the pontoon by the Alexandre III bridge at 6.30am Irish time, Wiffen will become the first Irishman to compete in an open-water swim at the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1558, \"to\": 1730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1626, \"end\": 1636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_the_Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Irish time\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_the_Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_the_Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere,Leona MaguireandStephanie Meadowwill return to Le Golf National for the third day of the women's Olympic golf tournament.\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1789, \"end\": 1805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Golf_National\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Golf National\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Golf_National\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Golf_National\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AndLara GillespieandAlice Sharpewill be back in action at the Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines Velodrome for the women's madison.\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1987, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"OPEN WATER SWIMMING  0630-0900Men's 10k marathon swim:Daniel Wiffen  GOLF  0800-1700Women's singles third round:Leona Maguire(0811) andStephanie Meadow(0822)  ATHLETICS  Women's heptathlon (Day 2):Kate O'Connor  Long jump from0905-0947  Javelin throw from1020-1102(Group A) or1130-1212(Group B)  800m from1915-1938  0930-0956Women's 4x400m relay (Heat 2):Sophie Becker,Phil Healy,Kelly McGroryandSharlene Mawdsl